        }
    ),
    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output='# Analysis of Satellite Deprecation Disclosure and Property, Equipment & Satellites Breakdown\n\n## 1. Is There a Separate Line Item for "Satellite Depreciation"?\n\n**No.** Based on the provided text chunks, there is no separately disclosed line item for "satellite depreciation" or "depreciation of satellites" in any of the three locations asked about:\n\n### Property and Equipment Note\nThe note presents a **single aggregate line** — "Less: accumulated depreciation and amortization" — with no breakdown by asset category (satellites, earth stations, CPE, etc.). The only exception is **CPE units**, for which the company separately discloses total cost and accumulated depreciation:\n- **March 31, 2025:** Cost $526.0M; Accumulated depreciation $328.0M\n- **March 31, 2024:** Cost $567.5M; Accumulated depreciation $267.4M\n\n### Segment Note\nNo separate satellite depreciation line item is indicated in the provided chunks for segment reporting.\n\n### MD&A\nThe MD&A discusses satellite launch cycles and mentions "depreciation, amortization of capitalized software development, earth station connectivity" as components of increased operating costs, but does **not** isolate satellite depreciation as a separate figure.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Total Net Book Value and Accumulated Depreciation Breakdown\n\n### Total Property, Equipment and Satellites, Net\n\n| | March 31, 2025 | March 31, 2024 |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Gross cost (total)** | **$11,440,273** | **$10,651,781** |\n| Less: accumulated depreciation and amortization | $(4,034,609) | $(3,094,575) |\n| **Net book value** | **$7,405,664** | **$7,557,206** |\n\n*(All figures in thousands of dollars)*\n\n### Gross Cost Breakdown by Asset Category (March 31, 2025)\n\n| Asset Category | Useful Life | Gross Cost (2025) | Gross Cost (2024) |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Equipment and software | 3–7 years | $3,837,083 | $2,992,325 |\n| CPE leased equipment | 4–7 years | $525,972 | $567,548 |\n| Furniture and fixtures | 7 years | $58,153 | $65,433 |\n| Leasehold improvements | 2–20 years | $313,249 | $209,162 |\n| Buildings | 12–38 years | $15,388 | $16,647 |\n| Land | — | $19,661 | $20,787 |\n| Construction in progress | — | $722,194 | $1,301,376 |\n| Satellites | 7–17 years | $3,405,067 | $3,324,458 |\n| Satellite Ka-band capacity (finance leases) | 7–15 years | $338,201 | $177,576 |\n| Satellites under construction | — | $2,205,305 | $1,976,469 |\n| **Total** | | **$11,440,273** | **$10,651,781** |\n\n### Breakdown of Accumulated Depreciation by Asset Category\n\n**This breakdown is NOT disclosed** in the provided text. The financial statements present accumulated depreciation and amortization as a **single aggregate figure** ($4,034,609K for 2025 and $3,094,575K for 2024). The only category-specific accumulated depreciation disclosed is for **CPE units** ($328.0M as of March 31, 2025; $267.4M as of March 31, 2024).\n\nFor all other categories — including satellites, earth stations, networking equipment, furniture, buildings, and leasehold improvements — the accumulated depreciation is **not separately broken out**.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| Question | Answer |\n|---|---|\n| Separate "satellite depreciation" line item? | **No** — not in the property note, segment note, or MD&A |\n| Total P,E&S net book value (2025)? | **$7,405,664K** (~$7.4 billion) |\n| Total P,E&S net book value (2024)? | **$7,557,206K** (~$7.6 billion) |\n| Accumulated depreciation by category? | **Not disclosed** (except CPE units: $328.0M in 2025, $267.4M in 2024) |\n| Aggregate accumulated depreciation (2025)? | **$(4,034,609)K** |\n| Aggregate accumulated depreciation (2024)? | **$(3,094,575)K** |',
